   By Jon Greenberg December 11, 2016

Reince Priebus falsely claims no conclusive report whether Russia tried to
influence election

   Reince Priebus, chairman of the Republican National Committee and
   President-elect Donald Trump’s incoming chief of staff, tried in an
   interview on Meet the Press to dismiss news reports that the CIA believes
   Russia aimed to boost Trump’s election chances.

Do you believe -- does the president-elect believe
   that Russia was trying to muddy up and get involved in the election in
   2016?"

Our ruling

   Priebus said that "there's been no conclusive or specific report to say"
   Russia was trying to muddy the election.
